[b]Adaptive Arithmetic Candles + Quality Score[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Replaces raw price bars with an efficiency-adaptive candle transform, then grades each candle's direction with a 0-100 Trend Quality Score so you can tell a trustworthy move from noise at a glance.

[b]Adaptive Candles[/b]
[list]
[*]Kaufman-efficiency-adaptive smoothing of a weighted close/typical/regression blend — reacts fast in efficient moves, damps in choppy ones
[*]Regression-anchored close with a trend-pressure body boost (slope + body strength)
[*]Synthetic wicks scaled from real wick proportions, widened when the market is noisy
[/list]

[b]Trend Quality Score[/b]
[list]
[*]0-100 score combining efficiency ratio, regression slope, body-to-range ratio, and follow-through vs. the prior close
[*]Strong vs. weak bull/bear candle coloring based on the score and regression-slope agreement
[*]Optional quality score line and high-quality dot markers
[/list]

[b]Flip Signals (early warning)[/b]
[list]
[*]Bullish/Bearish flip markers fire only when direction changes with quality ≥ 55 and regression-slope confirmation
[*]Optional labels showing the numeric quality score at each flip
[*]A flip alone is not a trade signal — it just marks a state change
[/list]

[b]Long/Short Signals (the actual trigger)[/b]
[list]
[*]Fire on a strong bull/bear state (quality ≥ threshold + regression-slope agreement) confirmed by a close breaking the prior N bars' high/low
[*]Structure break, not candle color, is what triggers the signal
[*]Built-in alerts for flips and for Long/Short signals
[/list]

